<br>
The GM's WILL rez you if you lose exp in the Arena.  GM told me that they do rezzes like anyone else: they have to get there before the rez timer runs out.  Exp loss from dots can happen under a couple circumstances:<br>
<br>
1)  If someone dies from a dot, and the person who cast it is no longer in the pvp area, exp loss will occur.  This actually happened the other night with Jaron.  He was dotted, but I died first and reapperaed at my bind point just outside the pvp door.  I wasn't thinking and sat down to mem spells.<br>
<br>
So... if you CAN dot, Necros, Shamen, Druids, you should bind just inside the pvp area.  Sit naked inside the pvp area and mem spells... no one will bother you.<br>
<br>
2)  Ever die and it says &quot;Pain and Suffering strikes you&quot;?  This means you fell unconscious, and rather than your red health bar going to zero exactly, you had that purple bar that appeared and went down.  This is what happened to ME the other night.  In these cases, EQ doesn't acknowlege that someone has slain you and it's possible you will lose exp.  <br>
<br>
To avoid this, just be alert around your comrades.  If you see a purple bar appear, your teammate or enemy is suffering and should be attacked quickly to be put out of his misery.  Sure, a heal could work and save him... IF he survives your cast time.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
